1. d4 e6!? { A flexible move order which invites the French Attack, and avoids a lot of annoying gambits of the traditional Dutch which stems from 1...f5. } 2. c4 (2. e4 d5 { Transposes to the French Attack! Check out this study to learn more: https://lichess.org/study/mr9g4cVe }) (2. Bf4 f5 { The London is another highly common opening setup for white these days. Check out chapter 3 the best way for black to attack in this opening. }) 2... f5 3. Nc3 (3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 d5 { The start of black's "Stonewall" formation. This is the recommended way to play against g3 setups which are commonly seen among strong players. See Chapter for more analysis. }) 3... Nf6 4. Nf3 { This development setup often combining Bg5, is one of the most popular setups for white at the amateur level. Check out chapter 2 for more analysis. } *


[Event "How to Play Against 1.d4: A Fun and Aggressive Opening Repertoire: Fighting the Typical \"Amateur\" Setup"]
[Date "2025.06.24"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "A84"]
[Opening "Dutch Defense: Classical Variation"]
[StudyName "How to Play Against 1.d4: A Fun and Aggressive Opening Repertoire"]
[ChapterName "Fighting the Typical \"Amateur\" Setup"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/RyMmCrx8/a1212Ocs"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/EricRosen"]
[UTCDate "2025.06.24"]
[UTCTime "05:57:50"]

1. d4 e6 2. c4 f5 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bb4! { It's best to pin the knight as soon as black has the chance. Black intends to capture on c3 to damage white's queenside pawn structure. } 5. a3?! (5. Bg5 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 h6 7. Bh4? (7. Bxf6 Qxf6 8. e3 b6 9. Be2 Bb7 10. O-O { Black will likely be having all the fun in the middlegame. There are 2 plans between attacking on the kingside and playing positionally against white's double pawns on the queenside. } 10... O-O { [%csl Ga5,Rc4,Gg4][%cal Gb8c6,Gc6a5,Gg7g4,Gd7d6] }) 7... g5 8. Bg3 f4 { trapping the bishop }) (5. Bd2 b6 6. a3 Bxc3 7. Bxc3 Bb7 8. e3 d6 9. Be2 Nbd7 10. O-O Ne4 11. Be1 O-O { [%csl Gg4,Rf3][%cal Gg7g5,Gg5g4,Gd8h4,Gb7g2] } (11... Qe7 { also possible to hold of on castling, and eventually castle queenside or put the king on f7. } { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gg7g4] })) 5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 { The following line will illustrate the optimal attacking setup for black... } 6... b6 7. e3 Bb7 8. Be2 d6 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Re1 Ne4 11. Bb2 Qe7 { [%cal Gg7g5,Gg5g4,Gb7g2,Gd7f6,Ge8g8,Gh8f8,Gf8f6,Gf6h6] } 12. Bf1 O-O 13. Qc2 Rf6 14. a4 Rh6 { Black's attack is pretty much unstoppable } { [%cal Gg7g4,Ge7h4] } *


