1. d4 e6 2. Bf4 f5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 (4. c4 { This is an invitation for Bb4+ since white no longer has c3 } 4... Bb4+ 5. Nc3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 { black is always happy to damage white's structure :) }) 4... b6 5. Be2 Bb7 6. h3 d6 7. O-O Nbd7 8. c3 { The following line illustrates how quickly black can generate a deadly attack if white is careless } (8. Nbd2 Qe7 { Another idea to stay flexible } 9. c3 h6! { preparing to attack with g5 next } { [%cal Gg7g5,Gg5g4,Gh6h5,Ge8f7] }) 8... Ne4 { [%cal Gg7g5,Gd8g5,Ge4g5] } 9. a4 g5 10. Bh2 h5 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gg5g4] } 11. a5 g4 12. hxg4 hxg4 13. Ne1 Qh4 *


