1. d4 e6 2. c4 f5 3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 d5 { Setting up the "Stonewall" formation } 5. Nf3 c6 6. O-O Bd6 7. Nc3 (7. b3 Qe7 { Preventing Ba3 } { [%csl Ra3][%cal Ge7a3] } 8. a4 { Now Ba3 is unstoppable, but white has now weakened the b4 square. Black can exploit this with the following sequence.... } 8... a5 9. Ba3 Bxa3 10. Nxa3 Na6 { [%csl Gb4,Ge4,Gg4][%cal Ga6b4,Gf6e4,Gg7g4,Ge8g8,Gc8d7,Gd7e8] }) 7... O-O 8. b3 (8. Bf4 Bxf4 9. gxf4 Ne4 { Lots of attacking potential for black } { [%cal Gf8f6,Gf6h6,Gb8d7,Gd8e8,Ge8h5] }) 8... Bd7 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gd7e8,Ge8h5] } 9. Bb2 Be8 10. Qc2 Nbd7 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Ge8h5,Gd8e7,Gf6e4,Gd7f6] } *


